{"type":null,"faqId":38035,"title":"My phone often disconnects from the Wi-Fi network on its own","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.s1{display: inline-block; text-indent: 0; min-width: 0.3048611in;}\n.s2{font-weight:bold;}\n.p1{text-indent:-0.2951389in;margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n <span>After successfully connecting to the Wi-Fi network, keep the phone within range of the Wi-Fi hotspot to avoid losing the connection due to a weak signal.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <span>For EMUI 2.0 and EMUI 2.3, select </span><span class=\"s2\">Wi-Fi</span><span> in the </span><span class=\"s2\">Settings</span><span> page to enter the Wi-Fi settings. Open the options menu, select </span><span class=\"s2\">Advanced &gt; Keep Wi-Fi on during sleep</span><span> and then select </span><span class=\"s2\">Always</span><span>. The phone will always stay connected to the Wi-Fi network.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <span>For EMUI 3.0, select </span><span class=\"s2\">Wi-Fi</span><span> in the </span><span class=\"s2\">Settings</span><span> page to enter the Wi-Fi settings. Select </span><span class=\"s2\">Advanced settings &gt; Keep Wi-Fi on during sleep</span><span> and then select </span><span class=\"s2\">Always</span><span>. The phone will always stay connected to the Wi-Fi network.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <a name=\"ZH-CN_TOPIC_0005065788\"></a><span>If the problem persists, turn off the Wi-Fi function and then turn it back on or restart the Wi-Fi hotspot.</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":281,"languageName":"fa","faqCode":"3255","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","modu